Package: JTNA
Type: Package
Title: Transition Network Analysis
Version: 1.6.0
Author:
  -  Dylan Girault [cre]
  -  Mohammed Saqr [aut]
  -  Santtu Tikka [aut]
  -  Sonsoles López-Pernas [aut]
Maintainer: Sonsoles López-Pernas <sonsoles.lopez@uef.fi>
Description: >-
    Provides tools for performing Transition Network Analysis (TNA) to
    study relational dynamics, including functions for building and plotting TNA
    models, calculating centrality measures, and identifying dominant events and
    patterns. TNA statistical techniques (e.g., bootstrapping and permutation
    tests) ensure the reliability of observed insights and confirm that
    identified dynamics are meaningful. See <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3706468.3706513" target="_blank">(Saqr et al., 2025)</a> for more details, <a href="https://github.com/sonsoleslp/JTNA" target="_blank">(Girault et al., 2025)</a> for JTNA, and <a href="https://doi.org/10.1177/01466216251348840" target="_blank">(Tikka et al., 2025)</a> for TNA.
